title: In relief to taxpayers, HC orders extension of date for revised return

description: Home Minister Amit Shah emphasized the Northeast's economic potential, highlighting its role as India's export gateway via the Chittagong port. He urged banking institutions to tailor financial guidelines to the region's unique context, fostering growth in infrastructure, agriculture, and MSMEs.
title: ‘Duty towards nation’: Amit Shah urges banks to frame special rules for NE

description: Home Minister Amit Shah, addressing the North Eastern Council, emphasized PM Modi's vision for the Northeast's development. He highlighted the significant infrastructure improvements, a 71% drop in violence, and the signing of peace treaties leading to over 10,000 armed youths joining mainstream society.
title: By 2047, NE to be India's most prosperous region: Amit Shah

description: The GST Council waived taxes on cancer gene therapy and reduced levies on fortified rice kernels.  Decisions on ATF inclusion, insurance rates, and food delivery services were deferred.  Used cars will face 18% GST, while pre-packed popcorn and voucher transactions saw clarifications.  A new GoM will address state-level disaster levies.
title: GST panel puts off call on lower rates for insurance
ASI team surveys 2nd temple in 2 days in Sambhal

description: Pakistan rebukes a US official's comments on its missile program, calling the allegations unfounded and harmful to bilateral relations. The Foreign Office defends Pakistan's right to maintain a credible minimum deterrence, emphasizing it poses no threat to the US and its missile development is purely defensive.
title: Pakistan slams US allegations on missile capabilities, warns against damaging ties

description: India's total forest and tree cover reached 25% of its geographical area, a slight increase since 2021.  However, the actual increase in recorded forest area was minimal, raising concerns among environmentalists.  Experts question the inclusion of plantations and trees outside designated forests in the assessment, emphasizing the need to focus on forest department efforts.
title: Experts debate ‘forest cover’ definition after release of forest survey report

description: India's 2023-24 forest fire season witnessed a decline in fire hotspots, attributed to improved wildfire management strategies.  Uttarakhand, Odisha, and Chhattisgarh reported the highest fire incidences.  Globally, Russia experienced the most significant tree cover loss due to fires from 2001-2022.  The Union environment minister expressed concerns and emphasized ongoing efforts to combat wildfires.
title: Forest fires down to 2.03 lakh in 2023-24 from 2.23 lakh in 2021-22

description: Pop star Taylor Swift, sporting a stylish red ensemble, attended boyfriend Travis Kelce's Kansas City Chiefs game against the Houston Texans. Joined by her parents, Swift's appearance marks her return to Arrowhead Stadium after skipping away games due to security concerns following a concert terror threat and Kelce's home invasion.
title: Taylor Swift attends Travis Kelce's game in a luxurious long red coat

description: Actress Blake Lively has launched a lawsuit against her 'It Ends With Us' co-star and director, Justin Baldoni, citing sexual harassment and a smear campaign. Lively alleges Baldoni fostered a hostile work environment, prompting a meeting with studio executives where she and husband Ryan Reynolds outlined several demands.
title: Blake Lively vs. Justin Baldoni: 'It ends with us' stars begin legal battle

description: Maharashtra's new government allocated portfolios a month after election results.  Chief Minister Fadnavis kept Home while Deputy CM Shinde secured Urban Development, Housing, and Public Works.  Deputy CM Ajit Pawar retained Finance and Planning, gaining Excise. Shinde's control over key urban bodies solidifies his position as second in command.
title: Maha portfolios: Fadnavis keeps home, fin with Pawar, Shinde gets urban dev

description: Former RBI Governor Raghuram Rajan revealed that ex-Finance Minister Arun Jaitley supported his decisive action on tackling bad bank loans. Rajan attributed the NPA surge to corruption, delayed clearances, and the global financial crisis. He also pointed to slow government recapitalization hindering lending.
title: Jaitley had given go-ahead to clean up bad loans, says Raghuram Rajan

description: The Election Commission of India modified electoral rules, restricting public access to poll booth CCTV footage, citing voter privacy and safety. This change followed a court order to provide such footage. Congress criticized the move as damaging electoral transparency and vowed legal action.
title: Candidates won't get poll booth CCTV footage: EC

description: India's total forest and tree cover reached 827,357 sq km, about 25% of the geographical area, showing a slight increase. While forest cover grew marginally, moderately dense forests declined. Chhattisgarh and Uttar Pradesh saw the biggest gains, while Madhya Pradesh experienced the largest decrease.
title: 25% of India under forest & tree cover: Government report

description: Gujarat police arrested three loan sharks.  The accused abducted a seven-year-old girl. They sold the girl in Rajasthan. The girl's father owed them money.  He could not repay the inflated debt.  The loan sharks forced him to sign blank papers. Police are searching for the girl. They are investigating the use of the blank papers.
title: Debtors sell girl for Rs 3 lakh to recover money from dad

description: UAE clinched a thrilling two-run victory over Kuwait in the ILT20 Gulf Cricket Championship (GCC) final.  Alishan Sharafu and Tanish Suri provided crucial runs for UAE.  Meet Bhavsar's 72 almost led Kuwait to victory.  The match went down to the wire.  Muhammad Jawadullah held his nerve in the final over.  UAE secured their first ILT20 GCC title.
title: ILT20 GCC: Late drama dents Kuwait as UAE lift maiden title

description: An LPG tanker collision with a truck near Jaipur left nearly 30 people with severe burns.  A nearby farming family provided refuge and, using a ladder, helped the victims over a wall to reach Kandoi Hospital.  The hospital staff administered first aid and swiftly transported the victims to SMS Hospital via ambulance.
title: Ladder turns lifeline: Burn victims scale 8ft wall to reach hosp in Jaipur mishap
Maharashtra initiates stringent action to deport illegal Bangladeshis

description: Congress is escalating its protests against home minister Amit Shah's remarks on Ambedkar, demanding his resignation. Nationwide protests, press conferences, and an 'Ambedkar Samman Saptah' are planned, culminating in a CWC meeting in Belagavi. The party will submit memorandums to the President and strategize further actions. Congress vows to defend Ambedkar's legacy against what they term "Manusmriti worshippers.
title: Protests in all dists, pressers in 150 cities: Cong to up ante against Shah

description: Left-wing extremism influence in India has shrunk significantly, from 18,000 sq km to 8,500 sq km in a decade.  A three-pronged strategy of intensified security operations, inter-agency coordination, and focused development has led to the neutralization of 287 Naxalites and the arrest of 992 in 2024.  Forward operating bases are facilitating development in reclaimed areas.
title: From 18,000sq km, Maoist-affected area down to 8,500sq km in 10 years

description: Thirteen lives were tragically lost in a fiery gas tanker explosion on the Jaipur-Ajmer highway. The NHAI attributed the accident to a temporary road cut, approved by a joint committee, while a cloverleaf interchange remains under construction. This cut, intended for U-turns, poses significant safety risks. A new contractor is tasked with completing the interchange by March 2026.
title: Rajasthan tanker explosion: NHAI defends U-turn, passes buck to panel

description: A car attack at a Christmas market in Magdeburg, Germany, left five dead and over 60 injured, including nearly seven Indian nationals. Three of the injured Indians have been discharged. A 50-year-old Saudi doctor is under investigation. Saudi Arabia expressed solidarity with Germany and condemned the violence.
title: 7 Indians among those injured in Christmas market car attack in Germany

description: AIMIM leader Akbaruddin Owaisi criticized actor Allu Arjun for his alleged insensitive response to a fatal stampede at a Pushpa 2 screening. Owaisi claimed Arjun, upon hearing of the death and injuries, remarked about the film's success and continued watching. Telangana CM Revanth Reddy condemned Arjun's actions and revealed the actor defied police denial of security permission for the event.
title: Actor said 'film going to be hit now' after stampede: AIMIM MP's big claim on Allu Arjun

description: A car plowed into a Christmas market crowd in central Germany on Friday evening, leaving five dead and over 200 injured, with nearly 40 in critical condition. Elon Musk reacted by demanding Chancellor Olaf Scholz's resignation, labeling him an "incompetent fool." Musk shared the alleged attacker's profile, criticizing Germany's handling of a prior extradition request from Saudi Arabia.
title: Elon Musk shares picture of German attacker's Twitter account; says ...

description: Mohammed Shami, recovering from ankle surgery, impressed fans with his powerful hitting during net practice at the NCA, even without helmet or pads. He recently returned to domestic cricket with strong performances in the Ranji Trophy and Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy, despite lingering knee swelling.
title: Shami steals the show with explosive batting in practice session

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi visited Kuwait, emphasizing India's support for Kuwait's development and praising the Indian diaspora's contributions.  He highlighted the growing partnership between the two nations, driven by shared economic aspirations and strong cultural ties.  Modi also interacted with the Indian community and acknowledged their role in strengthening bilateral relations.
title: India has skill, technology, manpower that 'New' Kuwait needs: PM Modi

description: Maharashtra Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis retained key portfolios including Home, Law, and Judiciary, while Deputy CM Eknath Shinde received Urban Development and Public Works.  NCP leader and Deputy CM Ajit Pawar secured the Finance Ministry.  The portfolio allocations, announced after weeks of negotiations, follow the recent cabinet expansion of the BJP-Shiv Sena-NCP coalition government.
title: Maharashtra portfolio allocation: CM keeps home ministry, Ajit gets finance

description: Congress plans nationwide protests demanding Home Minister Amit Shah's resignation for alleged disrespect towards Ambedkar.  The party has declared a week-long campaign including press conferences, marches, and a memorandum to the President.  They accuse Shah of mocking the invocation of Ambedkar's name during a parliamentary discussion on the Constitution.
title: 'Ambedkar Samman Saptah': Cong to hold nationwide marches over Shah's remark

description: Christmas, a cherished global festival celebrating Jesus's birth, fills the air with excitement and joy.  Homes adorned with lights and trees, carols evoke nostalgia, and the spirit of generosity prevails.  From exchanging gifts to charitable acts, the season embodies kindness and togetherness, enhanced by the whimsical tale of Santa Claus delivering presents.
title: Merry Christmas 2024: Top 50 wishes, messages and quotes to share

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi visited an Indian labor camp in Kuwait, highlighting his commitment to the diaspora's welfare.  He has consistently engaged with Indian workers abroad, addressing their concerns and implementing initiatives like the e-Migrate project to ensure safe and legal migration.  Bilateral agreements and relief efforts further demonstrate his focus on protecting Indian workers' rights and well-being.
title: PM Modi meets Indian migrant workers at labour camp in Kuwait

description: A Saudi doctor residing in Germany, Taleb al-Abdulmohsen, has been arrested following a fatal car-ramming at a Magdeburg Christmas market. German Interior Minister Nancy Faeser labeled the suspect as demonstrably Islamophobic. A refugee from Saudi Arabia, Taleb A, known for his anti-Islam activism and right-wing views, reportedly targeted the market in a suspected terrorist attack.
title: Christmas market attack suspect was clearly Islamophobic: German minister

description: Teenage batting prodigy Vaibhav Suryavanshi continues to shatter records. After becoming the youngest IPL signee last month, the 13-year-old debuted in the Vijay Hazare Trophy for Bihar, becoming the youngest Indian in List A cricket history.
title: Vaibhav Suryavanshi sets all-time record in Vijay Hazare Trophy

description: Congress opposed the changes made by Centre that restricted the public availability of certain electronic poll records.  Congress leader Jairam Ramesh said that the party will challenge the changes in court.  The ECI says the changes protect voter privacy. Congress, however, says the changes reduce transparency.
title: Why is ECI afraid of transparency: Congress after election rule tweak
'Character assassination': Actor Allu Arjun on stampede row after CM Revanth Reddy's criticism

description: Syed Zainul Abedin Ali Khan, Ajmer Dargah's spiritual head, lauded RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat's call to avoid new temple disputes.  Bhagwat's advice against creating further religious conflicts, particularly after the Sambhal Jama Masjid survey and the Ajmer Sharif Dargah petition, was praised as promoting national unity and progress. He emphasized the importance of harmony and acknowledged the Ram Temple's significance while discouraging further discord.
title: 'Commendable': Ajmer Dargah's head praises RSS chief for his remark on temples
Six-storey building collapses in Punjab's Mohali, several feared trapped

description: A Saudi doctor living in Germany drove into a Magdeburg Christmas market, killing five and injuring over 200. The 50-year-old suspect, an ex-Muslim with anti-Islamic views, was apprehended at the scene. Officials are investigating the motive, while the nation mourns and increases security measures.
title: German Christmas market attack: Death toll reaches 5, more than 200 injured
Refugee, doctor & Islamophobic: Man behind German market attack

description: Former chief selector Chetan Sharma backs Virat Kohli amid a lean patch, predicting three centuries in the Australia series. Despite recent struggles, Sharma remains confident in Kohli's abilities, highlighting his past contributions and expecting a strong finish in the remaining matches. Kohli's current form has been below par, but Sharma's belief in his resurgence remains unwavering.
title: 'Virat Kohli would score three centuries in Australia'

description: Travis Head's dominant batting performances against India, including crucial knocks in the World Test Championship and World Cup finals, have earned him the nickname "Travis Head'ache" from former India coach Ravi Shastri. Shastri praised Head's improved short-ball technique and aggressive mindset as key factors in his success against India's bowlers, particularly Jasprit Bumrah.
title: 'His new surname is Travis Head'ache'': Ravi Shastri

description: During the 2021 IPL, Ravichandran Ashwin astutely observed Steve Smith recording Delhi Capitals bowlers' techniques with a helmet camera.  Recognizing its potential use for analysis in the upcoming T20 World Cup, Ashwin halted his bowling, persuading teammates Axar Patel and Amit Mishra to follow suit, showcasing his sharp cricketing mind.
title: How Ashwin outfoxed Smith’s hidden camera trick

description: A man in California was arrested.  He allegedly killed his one-year-old son.  Police responded to a domestic disturbance call. The man's wife and mother-in-law escaped. The mother-in-law was injured.  The child was found beheaded inside the home. The man is in jail without bail.
title: California father arrested for allegedly beheading his 1-year-old son

description: Former Haryana Chief Minister Om Prakash Chautala, 89, passed away on Friday.  The five-time chief minister was cremated with state honors in Sirsa on Saturday.  Tributes poured in from across the political spectrum, acknowledging Chautala's contributions to Haryana's development and his championing of farmers' interests. His son, Abhay Singh Chautala, vowed to continue his father's legacy.
title: Former Haryana CM OP Chautala cremated with state honours in Sirsa

description: Ravichandran Ashwin's sudden retirement from international cricket during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy series has signaled the start of India's transition phase.  Aakash Chopra believes Ashwin's decision stemmed from limited overseas opportunities, exacerbated by Ravindra Jadeja and Washington Sundar's presence.  Chopra anticipates more retirements may follow, reshaping the team's composition in the coming months.
title: 'Ashwin retirement start of transition, next 3 weeks...'

description: BJP MLC C T Ravi, recently arrested and released for allegedly using derogatory language against a minister, claims a threat to his life and accuses the government of conspiracy.  He alleges being taken to isolated locations during his arrest and demands protection, holding the government responsible for his safety.  Ravi maintains respectful behavior and calls for a judicial investigation into police conduct.
title: ' ... if something happens to me': BJP MLC CT Ravi claims threat to life

description: India and Russia strengthened counter-terrorism cooperation during a joint working group meeting in Moscow.  Both nations discussed combating radicalization, terror financing, and the misuse of technology for terrorism. Russia reiterated its support for India's permanent UN Security Council seat, echoing endorsements from other world leaders.  India's bid highlights its growing global influence and peacekeeping contributions.
title: After UK, US & France, Russia back India's permanent UNSC seat bid

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi embarked on a two-day visit to Kuwait, marking the first such visit by an Indian Prime Minister in 43 years.  During his visit, Modi met with 101-year-old former IFS officer Mangal Sain Handa and individuals who translated the Ramayana and Mahabharata into Arabic, further strengthening cultural ties between India and Kuwait.
title: PM Modi keeps promise made on X, meets 101-year-old IFS in Kuwait

description: Telangana CM Revanth Reddy criticized actor Allu Arjun for attending a Pushpa-2 screening despite police denial, alleging his presence led to a fatal stampede. Reddy highlighted Allu Arjun's roadshow amidst the chaos and contrasted the support he received from film personalities with the lack of empathy for the stampede victim's injured son.
title: 'Pushpa 2' stampede: Allu Arjun was denied police permission, says Revanth Reddy

description: Virat Kohli is poised to surpass Sachin Tendulkar as India's highest Test run-scorer at the Melbourne Cricket Ground.  Kohli needs 133 runs to eclipse Tendulkar's 449-run record during the upcoming Boxing Day Test.  A strong performance could revive Kohli's form and solidify his legacy at the iconic venue.
title: Virat Kohli set to break Sachin Tendulkar's record

description: King Charles III, while visiting Waltham Forest, jokingly reassured the public about his health, saying, "I'm still alive." This marked the royal couple's final public engagement of 2024, where they celebrated community cohesion and donated to those in need. The King's cancer treatment, diagnosed earlier this year, is progressing positively and will continue into the new year.
title: 'I'm still alive': King Charles III jokes about health during London visit

description: US authorities are poised to blacklist Chinese chipmaker Sophgo, following the discovery of a TSMC-produced chip within Huawei's Ascend 910B AI processor. This suggests Sophgo illicitly supplied the chip to Huawei, violating US trade restrictions. Sophgo, linked to Bitmain, allegedly supplied chips to Chinese government entities, despite denying ties with Huawei.
title: US to ban this Chinese technology company for 'helping' Huawei

description: A devotee in Tamil Nadu accidentally dropped his iPhone into a temple's offering box.  The temple authorities and the HR&CE minister refused to return it, stating that anything offered belongs to the deity.  While the minister acknowledged the accidental nature, he cited temple rules and traditions.  A similar incident involving a gold chain was resolved with a personal donation from a temple official.
title: iPhone dropped in offering box now belongs to god: Minister

description: The government has revised election rules to restrict public access to electronic records like CCTV footage and webcasting videos. This change, following an Election Commission recommendation, aims to prevent misuse of sensitive data and protect voter secrecy. While candidates retain access, public access is now limited to specified documents, addressing concerns about potential manipulation and misinformation.
title: Govt amends election rules restricting public access to CCTV, other documents

description: A Varanasi woman was allegedly pushed from a hotel window by her boyfriend.  Priyanka Kumari suffered serious injuries.  She was in Varanasi for her graduation ceremony.  Her boyfriend, Furkan, kept her in the hotel against her will.  He has been arrested and jailed.  Priyanka is currently in the hospital.
title: Boyfriend arrested for 'throwing' woman from hotel's 3rd floor in UP

description: Delhi's Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena granted permission to the Enforcement Directorate to prosecute Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal in the liquor policy case.  AAP leaders expressed shock and called the reports fake, while the BJP labeled Kejriwal the "kingpin" of the scam. The high court granted the ED more time to respond to Kejriwal's challenge of the trial court's decision.
title: LG nod: BJP calls Kejriwal 'kingpin', AAP cries conspiracy

description: Tragedy struck off the Mumbai coast as the body of a 7-year-old boy was recovered following a collision between a ferry and a Navy craft. The search and rescue operations continue, with authorities working to determine the circumstances surrounding the devastating incident. The young boy's identity has not yet been released.
title: Mumbai boat accident: Police find body of missing 7-year-old boy

description: Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal announced a new scholarship for Dalit students, named after Dr. B.R. Ambedkar.  This followed recent political controversy sparked by Home Minister Amit Shah's remarks about Ambedkar in Parliament, which led to protests and disruptions, including physical altercations between MPs.  The opposition demanded Shah's resignation while the BJP accused the Congress of insulting Ambedkar.
title: Kejriwal announces scholarship scheme for Dalit students amid Ambedkar row

description: Prime Minister Modi invites everyone to experience the Rann Utsav in Gujarat's Kutch, showcasing its unique culture, arts, crafts, and historical sites like Dholavira.  The festival, running until February 28, highlights the region's transformation from past disasters into a hub of tourism and cultural preservation, recognized by the UN.
title: PM extends invite to attend Rann Utsav in Gujarat’s Kutch

description: Elon Musk called for German Chancellor Olaf Scholz's resignation following a deadly car attack at a Christmas market in Magdeburg, Germany. A driver plowed into a crowd, killing at least two and injuring over 60.
title: Elon Musk calls German Christmas market attack 'Deliberate mass murder'

description: D Gukesh, 18, won the World Chess Championship. He defeated Ding Liren.  Gukesh's family made a bold move. They took him out of school early. This allowed him to focus on chess.  His mother, Padma Kumari, shared their journey.  They faced doubts.  Gukesh's dedication reassured them.  His victory validated their decision.  He is now a champion.
title: 'Not sending Gukesh to school was tough call': Mother

description: Anmolpreet Singh etched his name in Indian cricket history with a breathtaking 35-ball century, the fastest ever by an Indian in List A cricket. During a Vijay Hazare Trophy match, Singh's explosive innings powered Punjab to a resounding nine-wicket victory over Arunachal Pradesh. His remarkable feat ranks third fastest globally, trailing only international stars.
title: Anmolpreet smashes fastest List A hundred by an Indian

description: Australian media created controversy by criticizing Ravindra Jadeja for answering interview questions in Hindi at the Melbourne Cricket Ground. The BCCI had arranged the interaction for Indian journalists, but some unaccredited Australian media attended.
title: Hindi-English row: Australian media stoops to a new low

description: Six people, including two children, were killed when a container truck toppled onto their SUV near Nelamangala, Bengaluru, on Saturday morning. The accident occurred on National Highway 4, causing a 3-km traffic jam. The family was traveling in a Volvo XC90 when the truck collided with another truck and fell on their vehicle.
title: Karnataka: 6 of family dead in horrific car accident

description: Drone attacks rocked Kazan, Russia, hitting residential buildings and prompting airport closures. No casualties were reported. This follows a deadly missile exchange with Ukraine, where Russia accused Ukraine of killing five in Kursk. Meanwhile, Ukraine claims to have downed 57 Russian drones and intercepted missiles aimed at Kyiv, though debris caused damage and one fatality.
title: Watch: Russia hit with 9/11 style attack on high-rise buildings; airport shut

description: Actor Darshan Thoogudeepa returned to his Mysuru farmhouse after being released on bail in the Renukaswamy murder case. His mother visited him shortly after his arrival. Darshan had received interim bail on medical grounds in October and was hospitalized. The farmhouse, owned by his wife, saw visits from family and friends.
title: Actor Darshan Thoogudeepa gets bail, returns to Mysuru farmhouse

description: India’s forest and tree cover has increased by 1,445 sq km since 2021, according to the India State of Forest Report (ISFR) 2023. Forest cover alone rose by 156 sq km, reaching 21.76% of the country’s total geographical area. Tree cover also expanded by 1,289 sq km. The overall green cover now stands at 25.17% of India’s land.
title: India’s forest and tree cover has increased by 1,445 sq km since 2021

description: Delhi's political scene heats up as AAP leader Arvind Kejriwal accuses BJP president JP Nadda of linking Purvanchalis with Rohingya and Bangladeshi immigrants. Kejriwal alleges a BJP plot to remove Purvanchali voters from electoral rolls, promising door-to-door campaigns to expose this "conspiracy.
title: Arvind Kejriwal claims BJP equated purvanchalis with Rohingya

description: Prithvi Shaw's struggles continue as he's excluded from Mumbai's Vijay Hazare Trophy squad due to fitness and attitude concerns. An MCA official criticized Shaw's fielding efforts and lack of discipline, revealing complaints from senior teammates. Former cricketer Jatin Paranjape condemned the MCA's public criticism, predicting Shaw's departure from the Mumbai team.
title: 'Not interested in helping Prithvi Shaw out': Ex-cricketer slams MCA

description: Melbourne Cricket Ground is bracing for an influx of nearly 100,000 fans for the Boxing Day Test between India and Australia. Security is being amplified, with extra personnel deployed to manage the anticipated boisterous crowd, particularly in the notorious blue stand area. Resale ticket markets are thriving, with fans paying significant premiums.
title: 'Notorious' stand, beer towers, Boxing Day madness: MCG braces for India vs Aus

description: At the MCG, Indian captain Rohit Sharma, under scrutiny for recent form, underwent intense nets practice.  He focused on spin bowling and his technique, receiving coaching from Abhishek Nayar.  Despite fan requests for sixes, Rohit maintained a serious demeanor, aiming to improve his performance in the upcoming Boxing Day Test.
title: Rohit nets session: No nonsense from fans to discussions over dismissals

description: Delhi's Lieutenant Governor has approved the Enforcement Directorate's request to prosecute Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal in the excise policy case. The ED alleges Kejriwal conspired with the "South Group" to receive substantial kickbacks and misused funds for AAP's Goa election campaign.
title: Delhi excise policy: LG V K Saxena nod to ED to prosecute Arvind Kejriwal

description: US President Biden approved $571.3 million in defence assistance for Taiwan, alongside State Department approval for a potential $265 million military equipment sale.  This aid bolsters Taiwan's defense capabilities amid heightened Chinese military activity and follows a similar aid package three months prior. Taiwan expressed gratitude for the continued US support in maintaining regional stability.
title: US president Joe Biden approves $571 million in defence aid for Taiwan

description: The National Centers for Environmental Information (NCEI), United States, released an updated version of the World magnetic model (WMM2025), forecasting shifts in Earth's magnetic field over the next five years. This model, which will remain valid until 2029, tracks the gradual movement of the magnetic north pole toward Russia. It also introduces a high-resolution update to ensure greater accuracy for navigation systems worldwide.
title: Magnetic north edges closer to Siberia, new model reveals

description: A Chennai policeman, Selvakumar, died tragically after falling onto an iron grille.  Following a drunken quarrel with his brother, he ransacked the house and became trapped on the grille while attempting to escape.  He was pronounced dead at a local hospital.
title: 'Grill 30cm into anus': Drunk Chennai policeman dies trying to escape through balcony

description: Facing internal dissent and mounting political pressure, Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau reshuffled his cabinet on Friday. This move follows the resignation of eputy prime minister Chrystia Freeland. With elections looming, Trudeau’s leadership is increasingly under scrutiny. Trump has also taunted him on social media, after threatening with tariffs, adding to Trudeau's woes.
title: Amid calls of resignation, Canada PM Justin Trudeau reshuffles cabinet

description: Zerodha's social media post highlighted the imbalance between work and personal life, sparking online discussions.  Using graphs, they depicted how much time individuals spend with colleagues versus family and pets, urging reflection on priorities and work culture's demands.
title: Zerodha founders on work-life-balance: If the realisation hasn't hit you yet…

description: PM Modi visited Kuwait to strengthen bilateral ties.  Congress criticized the trip.  They pointed to the ongoing violence in Manipur.  The party urged the PM to visit the affected region.  The violence started in May last year.  It involves clashes between the Meitei and Kuki communities.  Many lives have been lost.
title: Manipur continues to wait as frequent flyer PM is off to Kuwait: Congress

description: Former cricketer Michael Hussey recounted his first encounter with a young Jasprit Bumrah at the Mumbai Indians, where Bumrah's unusual action and sheer pace left him unable to connect with the ball. Despite initial skepticism about Bumrah's unconventional style, Hussey recognized his potential, even offering advice after a fiery send-off incident.
title: 'Felt like I was using a toothpick': Hussey recalls facing a young Bumrah

description: Virat Kohli's Bengaluru pub, One8 Commune, faces scrutiny for alleged fire safety violations.  The establishment, located in a high-rise building, reportedly lacks a fire department no-objection certificate.  Civic authorities issued a notice demanding clarification within seven days, threatening legal action if ignored.  This follows a previous complaint and highlights concerns about fire safety in similar establishments.
title: Virat Kohli's pub in Bengaluru gets civic body's notice

description: Militants attacked a Pakistani army post near the Afghan border, killing sixteen soldiers and critically injuring five.  Over 30 militants assaulted the post for two hours, destroying equipment and documents before retreating.  The Pakistani Taliban claimed responsibility, citing retaliation for the deaths of their commanders.
title: 16 Pakistani soldiers killed during attack on army post near Afghan border

description: Myanmar's Arakan Army rebels have seized a key military headquarters in Rakhine state, marking a significant escalation in the conflict against the ruling junta. This victory follows renewed fighting after a ceasefire collapsed last year. The AA's offensive, part of a broader resistance movement, has seen them gain ground, but also face accusations of targeting Rohingya communities.
title: Rebels deal heavy blow to Myanmar military, take control of key Rakhine base

description: Shreyas Iyer continued his dominant 2024 form with a blistering 51-ball century for Mumbai against Karnataka in the Vijay Hazare Trophy. His stellar year included leading Kolkata Knight Riders to the IPL title and Mumbai to the Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy.
title: 10 sixes! Shreyas Iyer hits 51-ball century

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman is leading the 55th GST Council meeting in Jaisalmer. AAC blocks with high fly ash content will now face a lower 12% GST. Conversely, used vehicles, including electric ones, see an increased 18% rate on sale.
title: Tax rate on popcorn revised, GST rate on sale of used cars increased: Report

description: Bill Gates credits his pre-smartphone childhood, filled with unstructured time and real-world adventures, for his success.  He suggests that today's phone-centric upbringing, lacking such freedom, hinders deep thinking and fuels mental health issues in teens. Gates contrasts his independent explorations with modern overprotective parenting styles that are surprisingly lax in the digital realm.
title: Microsoft founder Bill Gates has this ‘tip’ from his childhood for parents

description: Multiple projectiles launched from Yemen struck near Tel Aviv on Saturday, injuring 14 and marking a rare instance of Israeli defense systems failing to intercept.  Houthi rebels claimed responsibility, linking the attack to the ongoing Gaza blockade and vowing further action. This follows previous Houthi attacks and retaliatory Israeli strikes, escalating tensions in the region.
title: Houthi missile evades Israeli defenses, injures 14 in Tel Aviv
'Who was driving the car?': Vance, Musk slam 'legacy media' over misleading headlines
US Senate joins House in passing crucial spending bill: Key points

description: Indian cricket captain Rohit Sharma celebrated his wife Ritika Sajdeh's birthday with a heartfelt message on Instagram.  He's currently leading India in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy but has struggled with the bat, admitting his disappointment with his recent scores. Despite the lack of runs, Rohit remains confident in his preparation and mindset.
title: Rohit Sharma's emotional note on wife Ritika's birthday

description: Former cricketer Robin Uthappa, director of Centaurus Lifestyle Brands, faces an arrest warrant for alleged PF fraud. The company reportedly failed to deposit ₹23 lakh of employee PF contributions. Uthappa, currently residing in Dubai, is no longer at the Bengaluru address listed on the warrant, complicating its execution.
title: EPF fraud: Arrest warrant issued against ex-cricketer Robin Uthappa

description: Ravichandran Ashwin, India's second-highest Test wicket-taker, has announced his retirement from international cricket during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy.  Teammate Ravindra Jadeja acknowledged the significant loss but expressed confidence in finding a suitable replacement.  Ashwin's illustrious career includes 537 Test wickets, along with ODI and T20I contributions, marking him as one of India's greatest bowlers.
title: 'We have to move on': Jadeja on Ashwin's retirement

description: Alisha Parveen, who played Raahi in the popular show Anupamaa, has been unexpectedly replaced. Parveen expressed shock and disappointment at the sudden decision, stating she received no prior notice or explanation. Adrija Roy is reportedly taking over the role. This change comes amidst a popular romantic storyline involving Raahi, leaving fans wondering about the plot's future.
title: Adrija Roy replaces Alisha Parveen as Aadhya in Anupamaa?

description: A tanker truck carrying LPG collided with another truck on the Jaipur-Ajmer highway in Rajasthan, India, resulting in a massive fire that killed 14 people and injured 28 others.  The ensuing blaze destroyed 37 vehicles.  Prime Minister Modi announced compensation for the victims and their families. Authorities are investigating the cause of the accident.
title: Jaipur highway tanker collision death toll reaches 14, over 28 injured

description: Greg Chappell analyzes how cricket legends like Virat Kohli, Steve Smith and Joe Root face their eventual decline, termed "Elite Performance Decline Syndrome." He observes subtle shifts in their approach, marked by increased caution and a struggle to recapture peak fluency.
title: Virat Kohli, Steve Smith, Joe Root will decide their retirement: Chappell

description: Former India batting coach Sanjay Bangar has advised Virat Kohli to adjust his approach for the fourth Test at the MCG.  Bangar suggests Kohli play closer to his body, capitalizing on his strong record at the venue. He believes this adjustment will help Kohli regain his rhythm after a recent dip in form and contribute significantly to India's performance.
title: 'Surrender to the game': Ex-batting coach's advice to Kohli

description: In Rajgarh, Madhya Pradesh, a 32-year-old ASHA worker was brutally assaulted by her in-laws after a neighbor allegedly attempted to assault her. They accused her of infidelity, beat her, burned her with an iron, and inserted chili powder into her genitals. She was later abandoned at a dam but found by a passerby and hospitalized.
title: 'Burned with iron rod, red chilli in private parts': MP woman tortured by in-laws

description: Tragedy struck a Christmas market in Magdeburg, Germany. A car drove into the crowd. Two people died, including a child.  Sixty-eight others were injured.  A Saudi Arabian national was arrested at the scene.  Authorities are investigating the incident as a terror attack. The city is in shock.
title: Watch: Dramatic arrest of Taleb, who drove BMW into a crowd in Germany killing 2

description: The Kansas City Chiefs are determined to secure the No. 1 seed in their upcoming game against the Houston Texans. Tight end Travis Kelce is ready for the challenge despite a demanding schedule. Fans are eager to see if Taylor Swift will attend the game to support Kelce, adding to the excitement surrounding the Chiefs' playoff push.
title: Will Taylor Swift attend the Chiefs-Texans game to cheer for Travis Kelce?

description: Star spinner Ravichandran Ashwin retired from international cricket after the Gabba Test.  Harbhajan Singh dismissed rumors of a rift between them, praising Ashwin's achievements and emphasising mutual respect.  Harbhajan Singh clarified his criticism of spin-friendly Indian pitches, stating it wasn't directed at any individual. Ashwin picked 765 wickets in international cricket in 379 innings, while Harbhajan scalped 707 wickets in his illustrous career.
title: Harbhajan breaks silence on rift with Ashwin

description: Ravindra Jadeja expressed his deep sadness over Ravichandran Ashwin's surprising mid-series retirement from international cricket. Jadeja praised Ashwin as his on-field mentor, highlighting their successful partnership which yielded 587 wickets in 58 Tests. Ashwin, India's second-highest Test wicket-taker, retires with 537 wickets.
title: Jadeja pays tribute to 'on-field mentor' Ashwin

description: The Supreme Court slammed the misuse of temporary contracts.  The court highlighted the exploitation of workers, especially in the gig economy.  The court ordered reinstatement of sweepers who worked for two decades. The sweepers were employed by the Central Water Commission. The court ordered back wages for the sweepers. The court stressed fair employment practices for government organizations.
title: Gig economy led to precarious employment arrangement: Supreme Court

description: The Supreme Court clarified the scope of cheque bouncing cases. A director signing a company cheque for a personal loan is not liable under Section 138 if it bounces. The court emphasized the cheque must be from the individual's account. This decision impacts the 36 lakh pending cheque bounce cases. The director might still face cheating charges.
title: Director not liable if company cheque dishonoured: SC

description: Cricket legend EAS Prasanna believes lack of team support led to Ravichandran Ashwin's retirement. Ashwin, India's second-highest Test wicket-taker, retired after the Brisbane Test.  Prasanna felt Ashwin's overseas omissions impacted his performance. He compared Ashwin to Nathan Lyon, calling them classical spinners. Prasanna expects Ashwin to excel in coaching and mentoring roles.
title: 'Maybe indication that he [Ashwin] is no longer in the scheme of things'

description: India and France partnered to transform New Delhi's North and South Blocks into the Yuga Yugeen Bharat National Museum.  External affairs minister S Jaishankar highlighted this as a key cultural collaboration and a demonstration of India's soft power. The museum will showcase India's 5,000-year history and is envisioned as a global cultural landmark.
title: India, France sign pact for world's largest museum in Delhi

description: Hardeep Singh Puri and Shashi Tharoor clashed over a 2009 New York dinner with George Soros.  Puri said Tharoor, then a minister, gave him the guest list including Soros.  Tharoor had previously tweeted about meeting Soros.  The BJP questioned Soros's intentions toward India.  Tharoor denied any ongoing relationship or funding from Soros.  The BJP accused Congress of working with Soros.
title: 'Invitees list given by Tharoor': Hardeep Puri on 2009 dinner with George Soros

description: Abhinav Arora's lawyer, Pankaj Arya, filed a complaint in Mathura against YouTubers for allegedly trolling Arora and Sanatana Dharma. Arya stated they wouldn't spare the YouTubers and would pursue legal action up to the Supreme Court. A court hearing was held, and the next hearing is scheduled for January 3rd.
title: 10-year-old spiritual orator files complaint against YouTubers for trolling him

description: Tragedy struck a Christmas market in Magdeburg, Germany. A car plowed into the crowd. Two people died, including a child.  Sixty-eight others were injured. Fifteen are in critical condition.  The driver was apprehended.  Authorities are investigating the incident.
title: 'Blood on floor': Chilling experiences from Germany Christmas market car crash
Luigi Mangione 'to join notorious inmates in protective custody on Monday'

description: In Singapore, a 28-year-old Indian-origin man, Visnu Suriamurthi, received a six-week jail sentence and a SGD 2,000 fine for assaulting a rival gang member and illegal gambling.  This incident is connected to a fatal brawl outside Concorde hotel. Over ten men have been charged in connection with the brawl. Visnu’s sentencing took into account his history of violent offences.
title: Indian-origin man jailed in Singapore for violence and gambling

description: A Faridabad engineer fell prey to an elaborate online scam, losing Rs 3.46 lakh. Posing as courier and cyber cell officials, fraudsters accused him of possessing illegal items and involved in money laundering. They placed him under 'digital arrest,' monitoring him via video call for six days. He was tricked into transferring funds to a supposed 'RBI dummy account.
title: Mechanical engineer put under 'digital arrest' for 6 days, duped of Rs 3.46 lakh

description: Seth Meyers criticized Elon Musk's influence on Donald Trump and his stance on the government shutdown, comparing it to a dystopian "Christmas Carol."  The House passed a funding bill despite opposition from Trump and Musk, with Trump's team asserting his continued leadership within the Republican party.
title: Is Trump-Musk friendship doomed to fail? Seth Meyers predicts 'disastrous' future

description: PM Modi will visit Kuwait on December 21-22.  This is the first visit by an Indian Prime Minister in 43 years.  The visit will enhance ties between India and Kuwait.  Discussions will cover trade, defense, and energy cooperation.  PM Modi will meet Kuwaiti leaders and the Indian diaspora. He will also attend the Arabian Gulf Cup opening ceremony.
title: PM Modi's historic visit to Kuwait: All you need to know

description: Canada announced changes to its Express Entry program, impacting IT professionals seeking permanent residency.  The removal of extra points for LMIA-backed job offers will increase competition, requiring higher CRS scores based on factors like age, education, and language proficiency.  The changes follow recent revisions to broader immigration policies aimed at addressing housing and infrastructure challenges.
title: Express Entry: How new rules will impact techies seeking residency in Canada

description: Ravichandran Ashwin, India's celebrated cricketer, announced his retirement from international cricket after a remarkable 14-year career. In a candid interview, Ashwin and his wife, Prithi, shared their journey from schoolmates to life partners, offering insights into their relationship, the challenges of fame, and Ashwin's spontaneous proposal.
title: Ashwin's real-life partnerships: Prithi on love, parenting and fame

description: LinkedIn's COO, Daniel Shapero, reveals a crucial 2025 job interview question: "Tell me a story about how you used AI."  Employers are seeking AI-comfortable candidates as workplaces become AI-centric.  Successful answers range from professional to personal AI uses. This reflects the transforming job market, with AI skills becoming increasingly vital for navigating change.
title: LinkedIn COO tells techies most imp question they’ll be asked in job interviews

description: Ravichandran Ashwin's wife, Prithi Narayanan, penned a heartfelt tribute following the cricketer's surprising retirement announcement.  She reflected on their journey together, from his early days to his remarkable achievements, acknowledging the dedication and resilience that defined his career.  Narayanan encouraged him to embrace a life beyond cricket, free from the pressures of professional sport.
title: 'Love letter': Wife Prithi's message for R Ashwin

description: Australian cricketing legend Allan Border reflects on his illustrious career, from his playing days to captaincy challenges. He discusses aggressive batting in modern cricket, praising Travis Head's approach and Jasprit Bumrah's unique skill.
title: Exclusive: Any transition has to be gradual, says Allan Border

description: British Prime Minister Keir Starmer has nominated London-based professional Krish Raval for a life peerage in the House of Lords. Raval, chair of Labour Indians, awaits King Charles's approval. This nomination is among 30 aimed at balancing political representation. Raval, an OBE recipient for his inter-faith work, founded Faith in Leadership at Oxford University.
title: Who is Krish Raval? Indian-origin Labour Party figure nominated for Peerage

description: A pre-dawn missile attack on Kyiv killed one and injured twelve, damaging several embassies.  Ukraine intercepted the missiles and drones, but falling debris caused widespread damage. Russia claimed responsibility, stating the strike targeted Ukrainian military facilities.  Kherson also faced shelling, resulting in two deaths and ten injuries.
title: Russian attack on Ukraine: Embassies in Kyiv among damaged sites; one dead
US visa and H-1B overhaul in 2025: What Indian applicants need to know

description: Former Australian captain Allan Border praises Indian pacer Jasprit Bumrah's unique bowling style and captaincy skills.  Bumrah's impressive 21 wickets at an average of 10.90 in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy have made him the series' top wicket-taker. Border highlighted Bumrah's unusual wrist action and effective field placements, particularly during India's victory in Perth.
title: Jasprit Bumrah's presence has lit up this series: Allan Border
Delhi schools receive directive to identify illegal Bangladeshi migrant students

description: A pre-dawn collision between a truck and an LPG tanker on the Jaipur-Ajmer highway resulted in a series of explosions, killing twelve and injuring thirty-three. The impact ruptured the tanker, igniting a massive fire that engulfed over forty vehicles, including sleeper buses. Several individuals remain missing, including passengers of a bus and the tanker's driver.
title: ‘Gas gushed out like water from dam’: How Jaipur tanker crash triggered explosions

description: Eight idols were vandalized in Hindu temples across Mymensingh and Dinajpur districts over two days. One arrest was made in Mymensingh.  Five idols were damaged at a Dinajpur temple. These incidents follow other recent attacks on Hindu properties and come amid strained Indo-Bangladesh relations following the change in government and subsequent violence against minorities.
title: Three Bangladesh Hindu temples targeted again: Eight idols vandalised

description: A BJP MP gave Congress MP Priyanka Gandhi a bag with 'Genocide of Sikhs' written on it.  This happened at Parliament.  The bag referred to the 1984 events.  Gandhi initially accepted the bag. She later reacted to the message.  A Trinamool MP commented on the chairman's speaking time.
title: Priyanka Gandhi bristles as BJP MP gifts her 'Sikh genocide' bag

description: 'Pushpa 2' has now crossed Rs 1000 crore at the box office and the movie is now on its way to break the record of 'Baahubali 2' after beating 'Jawan' and 'Stree' by a huge number.
title: 'Pushpa 2' box office day 16: Film crosses Rs 1000cr, to beat 'Baahubali 2'

description: The House narrowly averted a government shutdown by passing a trimmed-down funding bill.  The legislation, supported by both parties, includes disaster relief and agricultural subsidies, but removed contentious provisions like a congressional pay raise.  The Senate now faces a tight deadline to approve the bill before the March 14th deadline.
title: US govt shutdown averted: House passes emergency funding bill

description: Tragedy struck a Christmas market in Magdeburg, Germany, when a car plowed into a crowd, leaving two dead, including a child, and at least 68 injured, 15 critically. The black BMW sped 400 meters towards the town hall before hitting market-goers. Disturbing videos circulating online appear to show the horrific incident.
title: Who is Taleb? Car driver behind Germany's Christmas market attack

description: Indian all-rounder Ravichandran Ashwin announced his retirement from international cricket after a decorated career spanning 13 years.  The off-spinner, who bagged 537 Test wickets, shared a heartfelt video tribute through BCCI, reminiscing about his journey and expressing gratitude for the support he received. Ashwin is the only Indian allrounder to score 3000 runs and take 500 wickets.
title: 'Thank You Ashwin': A heartfelt tribute and a secret promise
Earthquake of magnitude 4.8 strikes Nepal

description: A 55-year-old school principal in Maharashtra's Nanded district was found dead at his home, a day after allegedly drinking alcohol in a classroom. Students reportedly witnessed the incident and informed their parents, leading to a visit from education officials. A video of the inebriated principal also circulated. Police suspect he died by suicide, fearing public backlash.
title: School principal found hanging at home after being caught drinking in classroom

description: In Lucknow's Thakurganj, a chaat vendor, Rajesh Gautam, was fatally shot by a local goon, Rakesh alias Kalia, for demanding payment for chaat.  Kalia, arrested near Ghaila Bridge, confessed to the crime. Police recovered the murder weapon.  The accused has a criminal history and was planning to surrender.
title: Chaat vendor killed for asking goon to pay for chaat in UP's Thakurganj

description: A devastating highway accident involving a tanker truck collision sparked a series of explosions and fire, engulfing over 40 vehicles near Jaipur.  Eyewitnesses described horrific scenes of fleeing victims and burning vehicles.  The intense flames spread rapidly, leaving many trapped and causing widespread destruction.  First responders faced overwhelming devastation, with some victims burned beyond recognition.
title: Jaipur explosion: ‘Men, women scampering with clothes on fire; body in polybag'

description: A Jaipur gas tanker explosion left motor mechanic Radheyshyam Choudhary with 85% burns.  He bravely walked 600 meters while engulfed in flames, even calling his brother before succumbing to his injuries at SMS Hospital. Bystanders filmed his suffering rather than offering aid.
title: Jaipur tragedy: Man in flames walked 600m seeking help, but people just recorded videos

description: A devastating LPG tanker fire on the Jaipur-Ajmer highway claimed the life of police constable Anita Meena, identified tragically by her brother at the SMS Hospital mortuary. The chaotic scene saw families desperately searching for loved ones amidst confusion and restricted access to the burn ward.
title: Jaipur tragedy: ‘Recognised sister's toe ring,’ man’s 6-hr search ends in morgue

description: The Supreme Court cautioned women against misusing strict legal provisions intended for their welfare in divorce cases. The court emphasized that these laws are not meant for extortion, highlighting the misuse of accusations like rape and cruelty.
title: Strict laws are for women's welfare, not for extorting money from husband: SC

description: Lucha Libre pioneer Rey Misterio Sr., uncle and trainer of WWE Hall of Famer Rey Mysterio, passed away at 66.  Misterio Sr. wrestled for decades, last competing in 2023.  He significantly influenced professional wrestling, mentoring his nephew and other luchadores. AAA and the wrestling community mourn his loss, celebrating his enduring legacy.
title: RIP Rey Mysterio Sr.: Lucha Libre Royalty Dies at 66
